<BaseLayout title="About — Kunal" description="A bit about who I am and what I'm doing.">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    I'm Kunal. I build IT solutions for real-world business problems, the kind
    that look small until you live with them. Outside of work, I'm drawn to
    philosophy, psychology, and the slow practice of mindfulness, with a soft
    spot for Stoicism whenever life asks me to grow up a little more. I love
    cooking, long conversations, and arguing both sides of a position just to
    see which one holds. I'm working on becoming a better leader, helping the
    people around me become better versions of themselves, and staying curious
    enough to keep learning. This site is where I write what I'm chewing on.
  </p>

  <h2>What I do</h2>
  <p>
    I work on software for a living and on small apps for fun. I think most
    clearly through writing, which is why I keep a blog at
    <a href="https://thoughts.findkunal.com/en/">thoughts.findkunal.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://thoughts.findkunal.com/en/">Writing</a> — essays on what I'm thinking about.</li>
    <li><a href="/photos">Photos</a> — moments worth keeping.</li>
    <li><a href="/uses">My setup</a> — tools and gear I rely on.</li>
    <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a> — say hello.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
